### 1 # Create folders
################################################

Since tmux-powerline isn't in Arch repos, you will need to clone it somewhere in a folder

    mkdir ~/.bin
    cd ~/.bin
    git clone git://github.com/erikw/tmux-powerline.git

We'll have

~/.bin/tmux-powerline                   to store the original software
~/.bin/tmux-powerline-custom/segments   to store custom segments
~/.bin/tmux-powerline-custom/themes     to store custom themes

### 2 # Edit settings
################################################

Edit `~/.tmux-powerlinerc` and define the custom settings folder

	export TMUX_POWERLINE_DIR_USER_THEMES="/home/fradeve/.bin/tmux-powerline-custom/themes"
	export TMUX_POWERLINE_DIR_USER_SEGMENTS="/home/fradeve/.bin/tmux-powerline-custom/segments"

    cp ~/.bin/tmux-powerline/themes/default.sh ~/.bin/tmux-powerline-custom/themes/fradeve.sh

and edit `fradeve.sh` with your custom settings.

### 3 # Install useful software
################################################

%_SW_%		    %_NOTES_%
tmux
libmpdclient
rainbarf

### 4 # Explaining files
################################################

~/.rainbarf.conf                                rainbarf configuration file
~/.tmux-powerlinerc                             tmux-powerline config file with personal data and settings for
                                                each segment
~/.bin/tmux-powerline-custom/themes/fradeve.sh  defines which segments should be enabled and some
                                                appearence settings
